Thyroid dysfunction is one of the leading causes of hair loss in women. Given, there are many remedies to treat hair fall, some of which are extremely efficient, the best way to tackle the issue is to treat the underlying condition that is causing it. Following are 8 simple measures you could take to combat thyroid induced hair loss. But first, letâ€™s look at why thyroid dysfunction leads to hair fall.
<h2>How Thyroid Causes Hair Loss</h2>
Hair fall caused by the dysfunction of the thyroid is characterized by the loss of hair from all over the scalp; hair fall is not restricted to a single area. Both hyperthyroidism and hypothyroidism trigger this kind of hair loss. When a person undergoes treatment for thyroid, hair loss is curbed, but it almost never grows back with the same quality as before. Thyroid issues can also sometimes cause alopecia areata where hair fall is restricted to a particular area, and usually in circular patches. This can sometimes lead to unexpected baldness.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][vc_column width="1/3"][vc_widget_sidebar sidebar_id="hair_care_sidebar"][/vc_column][/vc_row]";s:10:"post_title";s:59:"8 Simple Ways To Combat Thyroid-Induced Hair Loss Naturally";s:12:"post_excerpt";s:0:"";s:11:"post_status";s:7:"publish";s:14:"comment_status";s:4:"open";s:11:"ping_status";s:4:"open";s:13:"post_password";s:0:"";s:9:"post_name";s:59:"8-simple-ways-to-combat-thyroid-induced-hair-loss-naturally";s:7:"to_ping";s:0:"";s:6:"pinged";s:0:"";s:13:"post_modified";s:19:"2017-04-20 11:49:40";s:17:"post_modified_gmt";s:19:"2017-04-20 11:49:40";s:21:"post_content_filtered";s:0:"";s:11:"post_parent";s:1:"0";s:4:"guid";s:41:"http://localhost/homemadesolutions/?p=663";s:10:"menu_order";s:1:"0";s:9:"post_type";s:4:"post";s:14:"post_mime_type";s:0:"";s:13:"comment_count";s:1:"0";}i:1;O:8:"stdClass":23:{s:2:"ID";s:3:"664";s:11:"post_author";s:1:"1";s:9:"post_date";s:19:"2017-04-14 13:15:49";s:13:"post_date_gmt";s:19:"2017-04-14 13:15:49";s:12:"post_content";s:1092:"[vc_row][vc_column width="2/3"][vc_column_text]Are you suffering from hair loss? Do you wonder if there is any remedy for the problem? Then garlic shampoo is what you should use!

Wondering how it can help cure your hair fall and improve the health of your mane? Keep reading to know more!
<h2>Why Use Garlic Shampoo For Resolving Hair Related Problems</h2>
Garlic, used mostly as a cooking ingredient in most households, has strong antibacterial and medicinal properties. This is why it was used by ancient civilizations to heal a number of skin ailments and serious diseases. Using garlic extract based shampoo can help in healing scalp infections and improving hair health greatly. Nowadays, you can also find deodorized garlic shampoos that eradicate the prospect of the hair smelling pungent! However, when you buy such shampoos, look for the other ingredients and the amount of garlic present in it. This plays a vital role in the efficacy of the product.

